## CONTENT STRUCTURE

**H1:** Best Almond Nail Colours for Every Skin Tone (2026 Guide)

**H2 Structure (10 H2s):**

1. **Why Your Skin Tone Actually Changes Everything About a Nail Colour**
   *(Brief but essential — sets the premise. Covers the core logic: same polish reads completely differently on different hands. Seeds the undertone concept.)*

2. **How to Find Your Undertone in 60 Seconds (Vein Test, Jewellery Test, Paper Test)**
   *(Practical, fast. Users need this before they can use the rest of the guide. Long-tail: "how to find undertone for nail color")*

3. **Best Almond Nail Colours for Fair Skin: What Flatters Without Washing You Out**
   *(Targets: fair/pale skin, cool + warm undertones. 2026 relevant: sheer pinks, soft lavender, icy blue, classic red, deep burgundy as contrast. Almond-specific note: sheer finishes extend the elongation effect on fair skin.)*

4. **Best Nail Colours for Medium Skin on Almond Nails: The Most Versatile Palette**
   *(Medium skin has the widest colour range. Coral, rose pink, mauve, berry reds, sage green, warm caramel nude. Note that medium skin "was simply made for red.")*

5. **Almond Nail Colours for Olive Skin: What Makes Golden Undertones Glow**
   *(Earthy tones, warm nudes, terracotta, warm reds, gold chrome. Avoids colours that bring out yellow cast. High search intent from olive-skin community on TikTok.)*

6. **Best Almond Nail Colours for Dark Skin: Shades That Actually Pop**
   *(High audience intent. Emerald, rich red, chocolate brown, cobalt blue, gold metallic, deep plum, true white contrast. Addresses the "wrong nude" problem explicitly. TikTok community strong signal here.)*

7. **Nude Almond Nails by Skin Tone: Finding the Shade That Looks Like Skin, Not Grey**
   *(Standalone H2 — this is one of the highest-frustration topics. Per-tone nude guide: cool-pink nudes for fair/cool, beige-latte for medium, warm cinnamon for olive, deep caramel/butterscotch for dark.)*

8. **The 2026 Almond Nail Colours That Work on Every Skin Tone**
   *(Universal colours: classic red, chocolate brown, deep burgundy, cloud-dancer white/milky sheer, champagne chrome. 2026 colour trends woven in — earthy neutrals, milky glazed finish, muted mauve. Natural hook for French tip internal link.)*

9. **Does Finish Matter? How Gloss, Matte, and Chrome Change a Colour on Your Skin**
   *(Differentiation angle: no competitor covers this in depth for almond specifically. Gloss adds radiance, matte can age, chrome reflects — all read differently by skin depth. Practical and genuinely useful.)*

10. **What Nail Colours to Avoid for Your Skin Tone (and Why They Go Wrong)**
    *(Pain-point direct address: "washed out," "looks grey," "doesn't suit me." Covers common mismatch traps: butter yellow on cool tones, very pale nudes on deep skin, harsh black on very fair skin. Honest, empathetic tone.)*

**Structure Reasoning:** The post opens with the *why* (sets authority), then equips readers with the self-knowledge tool (undertone), then moves through skin tones in a logical arc from fair to dark. The standalone nude section earns its own H2 because it's the single most-searched pain point in this category. The finish H2 is our clearest content gap win — no competitor covers it in this context. The avoidance section closes the loop on the frustration the reader arrived with. Internal links thread naturally throughout: almond-nails-guide in the intro, almond-nail-ideas in the mid-section, french-tip-almond-nails in the universal section, press-on in the close.

