## VOICE & TONE RECOMMENDATION

**Recommended Voice:** Informed friend who knows her colour theory — warm, direct, and specific. Not a beauty editor speaking at readers. Not a brand pushing products.

**Tone Characteristics:**
- Empathetic — acknowledges the real frustration of a colour that looked right and wasn't
- Confident and specific — gives concrete shade families, not vague advice
- Conversational but credible — references nail tech expertise and 2026 trend sources without being academic
- Inclusive — speaks to every skin tone as equally important; no skin tone is treated as "the norm"
- Practical — every section ends with something actionable

**Language Style:** British English throughout (Mirellè editorial standard). Use "colour" not "color" in body copy. Address reader as "you" directly. Avoid technical jargon without brief explanation. Short sentences work well in the skin-tone sections — they read cleanly alongside images.

**Audience Match:** Reader has almond nails or wants them; she's landed on this page because a colour didn't work out (reactive) or because she's planning her next appointment and wants to get it right (proactive). Both want certainty, not options paralysis. The voice gives her the clarity she came for.

